I have just formed my guild, Mercenaries of Lanys, and we are looking to form alliances with some of the better guilds on the server. (Notice I did not say more powerful guilds, just better. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) My guilds basic premise is that we are more casual players that have a hard time being in guilds that have a harsh raid schedule requirement. On the same note, we do enjoy going on raids, so, our solution is to form a guild who specializes in assisting other guilds in helping them do raids that they would normally not have the man/woman power to do. In exchange for our help, we ask that our members who assist you in your raids be allowed Fair chances at looting rights for drops that they may want on the raids that you run. In some cases, when loot is not an issue to the member, possible assistance to that same member for a quest/item at another time might also be a fair exchange.<br>
<br>
Mercenaries of Lanys also plans to sponsor open raids that your guild would be more than welcome to attend if any of your members would like to join us in raids that would normally be reserved for the larger/more powerful guilds. Tuesday nights Ring of Fire raid is proof that all types of people can work together, bringing the Lanys community closer together as a whole.<br>
<br>
Our membership is small right now, but, we are growing little by little. Please drop by our message boards and say hello. If your guild needs some help with something, please feel free to post and ask for our assistance.<br>
<br>
Thank you. Be well<br>
-Worthy Iam, Guild leader Mercenaries of Lanys <br>
